<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<?xml-stylesheet type='text/xsl' href='/xml/xsd2html2xml/xsd2html2xml.xsl'?>
<recipe xmlns="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io"
        xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
        xsi:schemaLocation="https://cazzscookingcommunity.github.io ../../xml/recipe.xsd">
  <title>Rum Balls</title>
  <filename>rum_balls.xml</filename>
  <thumbnail>rum_balls.jpeg</thumbnail>
  <category>Sweets</category>
  <ingredient>1 packet Marie biscuits crushed</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 can sweetened and condensed milk</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1 TBsp desiccate coconut</ingredient>
  <ingredient>2 TBsp cocoa</ingredient>
  <ingredient>1-3 drops rum essence (optional)</ingredient>
  <ingredient>Extra coconut</ingredient>
  <step>Mix all ingredients in a bowl except extra coconut with a big spoon.</step>
  <step>Scoop out about one teaspoon at a time and roll into ball in the palm of your hands, then roll in extra coconut, until completely covered.</step>
  <step>Refrigerate for 2 hours, before serving.</step>
  <step>Can be made up to one week in advanced if kept in air tight container.</step>
  <step>You can double this recipe.</step>
  <step>In hot  weather you may have to refrigerate before rolling into balls.</step>
</recipe>
